SIMPLE: portable
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Portable
<hw>Port"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>portabilis</ets>, fr. <ets>portare</ets> to carry: cf. F.
<ets>portable</ets>. See <er>Port</er> demeanor.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being borne or carried; easily transported; conveyed
without difficulty; <as>as, a <ex>portable</ex> bed, desk,
engine</as>.</def> <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Possible to be endured; supportable.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How light and <qex>portable</qex> my pain seems now!</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Portable forge</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Forge</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Portable steam engine</b></col>. <cd>See
under <er>Steam engine</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Portableness</ent>⟦br⟧
